news.title: Nashik civic body to spend Rs 11 crore on 3,200 new street lights
news.para: Municipal commissioner Chandrakant Pulkundwar has proposed the installation of the streetlights from the financial provisions made in the civic budget for the financial year 2023-24.

news.title: Gurugram court directs police to initiate process to declare former IREO CEO a proclaimed offender
news.para: The order was issued after an arrest warrant against him returned unexecuted. The court said it "is satisfied that the presence of the accused Ramesh Sanka cannot be secured through issuance of non-bailable warrants".

news.title: Strict action being ensured against illegal constructions in green belt: Haryana minister
news.para: Detailed information about such buildings, whether they are residential or commercial, their construction period, action taken and FIRs registered, was placed on the table of the House.

news.title: Cut power, water to unauthorised Trichy building, says Madras HC
news.para: The court was hearing a petition filed by A Jalal seeking for a direction to the Trichy corporation authorities to inspect the three-storey building at Kalaivanar Street at Sangiliyandapuram in Trichy and grant approval and stability certificate.

news.title: Chandigarh heritage committee to meet on Mar 27 to discuss on apartmentalisation
news.para: The SC judgement, which came in January, banned apartmentalisation or fragmentation of residential units in the city. The CHCC was given the mandate to preserve the heritage status of ‘Corbusian Chandigarh’.

news.title: 315Work Avenue leases 25,000 sq ft to Urban Company in Bengaluru
news.para: Located at Krimson Square, HSR Layout, this new office of Urban Company is expected to house more than 500 employees.

news.title: Jaipur development body razes four illegal colonies
news.para: While two of this colonies fall under jurisdiction of zone 14 of the civic, the rest two were coming up at the ecological zone under the jurisdiction of zone 10.

news.title: Ganga Realty to invest Rs 750 crore to develop affordable housing project in Gurugram
news.para: Spread across approximately 22 acres, Ganga Realty's Tathastu project will offer 3 BHK apartments with carpet area of 645.73 sq ft at a price of Rs 25.14 lakh.

news.title: Andhra Pradesh government waives interest on property tax dues
news.para: Y Srilakshmi said the decision to waive the interest on the old dues was taken as a one-time incentive to provide relief to all those who could not pay the taxes in the last two years due to the lockdowns following the outbreak of Covid-19.

news.title: About 9.22 lakh families left out of PMAY: Rajasthan rural development minister
news.para: He said that the central government is being urged to upload these deprived families on Awas Plus. He said that there was no negligence on the part of the officers and employees of the department in this matter.

news.title: Enforcement directorate searches three sites to spot PMAY scam
news.para: The ED has registered a money laundering case against the builders based on an FIR registered at Chhatrapati Sambhajinagar city police station on February 23.

news.title: Noida authority sets up a panel to inspect STPs in societies
news.para: According to officials, a Delhi-based company has been hired to inspect STPs and ensure that they are properly functioning. The team will be provided space in the Noida Authority office.

news.title: Haryana RERA directs Splendor Landbase to pay fine with interest to home buyers
news.para: The authority also set aside a unit cancellation notice issued by the builder — Splendor Landbase Limited — on February 7.

news.title: Bombay HC restrains Avarsekar Realty from selling unsold flats across projects
news.para: Bombay high court recently restrained a builder, Avarsekar Realty Pvt Ltd, from selling any of its unsold flats as on date in a proposed plush 42-storey highrise at Mahim and its other projects till further orders.

news.title: Colliers India's CEO Ramesh Nair resigns
news.para: According to sources, Nair resigned as Colliers India CEO on Friday with immediate effect to pursue external opportunities. He was also Managing Director, Market Development for Asia, at Colliers.
